articles.author: Sheila Chiang
articles.title: Intel wants to build 'everybody's AI chips,' CEO says, as company plays catch-up with rivals - CNBC
articles.description: Intel wants to regain leadership in the chip industry after losing market share opportunities to rivals, its CEO said.
articles.content:
Intel wants to regain its position as the world's leading chipmaker, CEO Pat Gelsinger said, after being overtaken by rivals TSMC and Samsung in recent years.

articles.author: Patrick Wingrove
articles.title: Britain considers offering Lilly weight-loss drug on better terms than Wegovy - Reuters
articles.description: Britain's medical costs regulator on Tuesday recommended Eli Lilly's weight-loss drug Mounjaro for some patients with obesity and suggested not placing a time limit on the medicine's use as it had for rival Novo Nordisk's Wegovy.
